	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65030781"><p>So what? EU laws don't actually apply to any country. Countries (including EU member nations) are required to individually pass laws that adopt EU directives. In this case Switzerland despite not being in the EU has in fact passed a law fully compliant with the EU Radio Equipment Directive and as such just like the rest of the EU on the 28th December 2024 it will be illegal to market and sell a phone in Switzerland that can't be charged via USB-C. They are also not the only country to do this.</p></div>
